# Git workflow

- **Always commit** after completing a change. Do not wait for a trigger word.
  Run `git status`/`git diff` first, then stage the allowed files and commit.
- **Commit messages:** short, imperative, English. One logical change per commit.

```text
add fastq per-position quality metric
fix vcf ts/tv ratio rounding
update compose postgres memory cap
```

- **Never commit markdown files, except `README.md`** (any folder). Files like
  `AGENT.md`, `plan.md`, and `docs/*.md` must stay local and be excluded when staging.
  This is enforced by convention here, **not** by `.gitignore` — do not add these to
  `.gitignore`. When staging, add files explicitly instead of `git add .`, or unstage
  any non-README `.md` before committing.
- **Do not push automatically.** Push only when the user explicitly asks.
- Never commit secrets or the `data/` runtime folder.
